fining trans life, thought, and creativity, forms of maladjustment have also been and will continue to be central to their development.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDisability studies. 0aFeminist theory. 0aGender identityxPsychological aspects. 0aGender nonconformityxPsychological aspects. 0aQueer theory. 0aTransgender people. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Transgender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023302?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023302423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023302/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles